  "text": "Bacterial Strains, Plasmids, and Growth Media-Escherichia coli DH5 (recA1) was used for plasmid maintenance and cloning. E. coli DH5 lacI::Tc, in which the lacI gene is disrupted by Tn10, was constructed by P1 transduction from E. coli N99 lacI::Tc (29) into DH5 that was transiently recA ϩ as described previously [CITATION_1] . DH5 lacI::Tc (parAB) is a parAB lysogen ( i21 phage containing P1 parAB, constructed as described in Ref. [CITATION_2] ). DH5⌬lac (parOP-lacZ), described previously [CITATION_3] , was the reporter strain for ␤-galactosidase expression. Briefly, parOP-lacZ contains a translational fusion of lacZ with the start of parA from the par operon, in i21 phage. E. coli BL21 DE3(pLysS) was used for protein expression. Plasmids used in this study are listed with relevant genes in Table 1 and described  in supplemental Table S1 .",
